Description: Small corroded iron chisel or wedge, with rectangular cross-section; slightly convex large sides tapering to a cutting edge at one end; the other end is barely larger and has a small central lump.
Curator's comments: Probably one of the "chisels (...), of which about forty were kept, beside many rejected", mentioned by Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 78 § 78.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 78 § 78)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.47, p.75, p.184, pl.26)
